# FAQ - Payments
faq-pay-q1 = What payment methods do you accept?
faq-pay-a1 = We currently use Cryptocurrency (e.g BTC, BCH, LTC, XMR, etc.) as the main method of payment. While it may be inconvenient to use for the first time, it will always be reliable. When you checkout, make sure you have the funds ready to send.

faq-pay-q2 = What is the easiest way to pay with crypto?
faq-pay-a2 = If you would like to pay with crypto, the easiest way to obtain it is through an exchange. There are hundreds of exchanges, but notable ones include <a class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline" target="_blank" href="https://coinbase.com">Coinbase</a>, <a class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline" target="_blank" href="https://www.paypal.com/us/digital-wallet/manage-money/crypto">Paypal</a>, <a class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline" target="_blank" href="https://crypto.com">Crypto.com</a> and <a class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline" target="_blank" href="https://www.revolut.com/crypto/">Revolut</a> (may take 24h). If you would like to purchase through a decentralized exchange, there is also <a class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline" target="_blank" href="https://bisq.network/">Bisq (BTC)</a>. It may take a little time to set up if you are using it for the first time, but it is quite easy for subsequent payments.

faq-pay-q3 = Why is my payment taking so long?
faq-pay-a3 = Depending on network congestion, crypto payments may take up to an hour to fully process. Normally payments are complete within 5 minutes. Sometimes cryptocurrency exchanges delay withdrawls which may make payment take a bit longer. If your payment is not confirmed after many hours, <a class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline" href="/contact">contact us</a>.

faq-pay-q4 = Do you accept refunds/returns?
faq-pay-a4 = We do not provide guaranteed refunds or returns at this time. However if you have a problem with your order, please <a class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline" href="/contact">contact us</a>. More information about terms of ordering can be found on our <a class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline" href="/policies">Policies</a> page.

faq-pay-q5 = Do you have any hidden fees?
faq-pay-a5 = No, we do not have any hidden fees or taxes, everything is included in the product and shipping price. Tariffs are also included in shipping costs if they apply.

# FAQ - Products
faq-prod-q1 = What are PBIOs?
faq-prod-a1 = PBIO Listings (e.g PBIO-4D) are our custom-named products. PBIO stands for PENCHANT BIO. Most of the time, we name compounds with our prefix if the compound is a custom product or has no professionally designated name. The only exception to this is PBIO-4D. PBIOs can be found <a class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline" href="/collections/pbios">here</a>.

faq-prod-q2 = What products will you list next?
faq-prod-a2 = Our main focus is developing effective cognitive enhancers, notably molecules/combinations of molecules that the forebrain. This is the priority, though tangentially related projects are being developed at the same time. If you want updates on new products, you can follow our twitter page (<a class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline" target="_blank" href="https://twitter.com/penchantbio">@PenchantBio</a>).

faq-prod-q3 = Why are products out of stock often?
faq-prod-a3 = We have high demand for some products, which means that they may run out. We've added stock tracking to make it more clear what products are low in quantity. We restock products as fast as possible, so please be patient. As we increase our catalog, products being out of stock will be a more rare occurance.

faq-prod-q4 = Why is benzyl alcohol in sprays?
faq-prod-a4 = We put benzyl alcohol in some products as a method of sterilization. We notably do this for peptides and some molecules dissolved in water. Our standard concentration for vertical sprays is 0.8%.

faq-prod-q5 = How should products be stored?
faq-prod-a5 = It is ideal for most products to be stored in a dark, dry place as it extends lifepan. For peptides or products with the ❄! symbol, they should ideally be refrigerated if they will be stored for 1+ months. Reconstituted Aquilots/Vials should always be refrigerated unless noted otherwise.

faq-prod-q6 = What is the purity of your products?
faq-prod-a6 = Our products have a standard of ≥98% purity, and for natural/naturally-derived products the purity standard is ≥95%. We measure the purity with testing methods such as QNMR (Quantitative Nuclear Magnetic Resonance) and HPLC (High-performance Liquid Chromatography), which provide an accurate measurement of product purity. Analysis results can be found on product pages, and these are done with a third party, whose results can be verified by anyone who is interested.

faq-prod-q7 = How do you offer such competitive pricing?
faq-prod-a7 = We are able to provide competitive prices by purchasing in large volumes and through direct networking with suppliers. When we purchase materials in large quantities, we make novel compounds available at the lowest prices on the market, while also maintaining being profitable. We derive our prices from operational costs plus a margin which allows us to reinvest in the development of new products.

faq-prod-q8 = What is the margin of error for products?
faq-prod-a8 = We have a total margin of error of ±5% for contituent volume & constituent potency (e.g mg/mL) for all products unless otherwise mentioned.

faq-prod-q9 = How many mL do the sprays eject?
faq-prod-a9 = For our white-topped vertical sprays, they spray 0.095-0.1mL per ejection, so ~10 sprays per mL. We have switched from the previous black-topped sprays as the white variant have clips to prevent accidental sprays in transit. More detailed information can be found on spray bottle labels.

# FAQ - Miscellaneous
faq-misc-q1 = Can I buy in bulk?
faq-misc-a1 = Yes we are able to sell our products in bulk quantity, you can <a class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline" href="/contact">contact us</a> via email for more information. Bulk pricing generally starts at 20+ products.

faq-misc-q2 = Do you offer custom synthesis?
faq-misc-a2 = Yes, for most molecules, including nootropics and peptides, we can develop and source them. Please keep in mind the minimum order quantity for novel molecules may be large. If you would like to inquire about this, please <a class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline" href="/contact">contact us</a>.

faq-misc-q3 = Is pricing more expensive in different countries?
faq-misc-a3 = Pricing is usually the same accross countries. We factor local taxes and costs into the standard pricing for products. The only main difference between regions is shipping cost.

faq-misc-q4 = Do you have any reviews?
faq-misc-a4 = Yes, you can check our <a class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline" target="_blank" href="https://www.trustpilot.com/review/noveldist.com">Trustpilot</a> for reviews, or you can directly ask the many satisfied customers who have purchased from us.

faq-misc-q5 = What is the TFA content of peptide products?
faq-misc-a5 = To meet quality standards, peptides listed have <1% TFA.

faq-misc-q6 = How do you calculate the potency of products?
faq-misc-a6 = We generally base the potency of our products on studies and references to meet the estimated efficacious dose (ED). <a class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline" href="/policies">This does not constitute advice of consumption</a>. Our standard for the ED of sprays is 2 ejections and generally 0.5mL for dropper bottles.

